Sanlam to Spend $266 Million on 26% Stake in India’s Shriram Capital

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-09-08T06:24:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/sanlam-to-spend-266-million-on-26-stake-in-india-s-shriram-capital.html
Sanlam Ltd. (SLM) , a South African
insurer, said it will invest 1.9 billion rand to buy a 26
percent stake in  India ’s Shriram Capital as it expands its life
and casualty and property cover businesses outside its home
market.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
